-- HELLO-PF: "Hello World" via Port B, polyForth-style
--
-- Mirrors the architecture of polyForth's serial terminal nodes
-- (pFDISK.blk blocks 1995/1996), loaded via HOST LOAD to Port B.
--
-- Node 200 (pin17 ← Port B RX): auto-baud from first incoming byte,
-- receives bytes and relays them UP to node 100.
--
-- Node 100 (pin17 → Port B TX): receives baud calibration from node 200,
-- then for each trigger byte sends "HELLO WORLD\r\n" using polyForth's
-- putchar / !bit protocol.
--
-- TX bit encoding (non-maxim EVB002):
--   mark/idle = x25555 (pin17 low),  space/start = x35555 (pin17 high)
--   matches polyForth block 1995: "start hi, data 1 is low"
--
-- Both nodes communicate via their shared UP port (0x145).
-- Load to Host chip via HOST LOAD (Port B = Host nodes 100/200).

-- ============================================================
-- RX NODE (node 200 — one-wire boot node, pin17 ← Port B RX)
-- ============================================================

node 200

